CHEF'S SUGGESTION
Yum Makeua Yao
(Thai Green Aubergine Salad)
INGREDIENTS
fresh green aubergine
Boiled prawns
Boiled egg wedge
20
grams x 8 pieces
gramsao preces
pieces
DRESSING
Fish sauce
Fresh lime juice
Brown sugar
Juice of pickled garlic
Crushed red chilli
grams
grams
grams
GARNISH
Shallot, peeled, sliced
Red chilli, julienned
16
Coriander leaves
Pickled garlic (Kratiem dong)
Ground dried shrimp
40
80*
grams
HOW TO PREPARE
- To make the dressing, combine all the ingredients together and
stir until the brown sugar has dissolved, set aside.
- Grill over charcoal, moderate heat and
remove the skin of
green aubergine, cut into 1 inches long and cut them in quarter
lengthwise, then place on serving dish.
- For serving : Pour dressing as preferable over green aubergine
and layer with sliced shallot, ground dried shrimp, and garnish with
egg wedge, boiled prawns, julienne of red chilli.
Note : For those who prefer more or less spicy taste, can adjust
chilli as require.
TG 992 Y - FEB/MAY / AUG/NOV
